()🚀 TaskDefinition kya hai?
👉 TaskDefinition:-
👉 Ye ek configuration object hota hai jo batata hai task kya karega
💡 Simple Definition:-
👉 TaskDefinition = “Task ka blueprint / design”
👉 “TaskDefinition SailPoint me task ka configuration object hota hai jo define karta hai ki task kya karega aur kaise karega.”

🔥Isme kya-kya hota hai?
👉TaskDefinition me hota hai:-
Task ka naam
Arguments (input parameters)
Schedule
Owner
Description

💡 Simple Samajh (1 line):-
👉 TaskDefinition = kya karna hai
👉 Task = kaam kar raha hai (execution)

🔥 Detailed Difference Table:-
Feature	          TaskDefinition	                Task
Meaning      	Blueprint / Config	              Actual execution
Role	      Define karta hai task kya karega	Task ko run karta hai
Data	          Static (config)	            Dynamic (runtime)
Change hota hai?	Rarely	                      Har run me
Output	           ❌ nahi	                 ✅ TaskResult deta hai
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------





















----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🚀 TaskDefinition ke Types:-
👉 SailPoint me mostly ye common task types use hote hain:-
Aggregation
AccountAggregation
IdentityRefresh
Provisioning
Certification
Report
LiveReport
Workflow
Rule
Maintenance
SystemMaintenance
TaskExecution
DataExport
DataImport
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 Aggregation:-
👉 External system se data pull karna (accounts/users)
Example: AD se users lana

🔹 AccountAggregation:-
👉 Sirf accounts ka aggregation
Example: Sirf user accounts sync karna

🔹 IdentityRefresh:-
👉 Identity ko recalculate/update karna
Example: roles, entitlements refresh

🔹 Provisioning:-
👉 System me account create/update/delete karna
Example: AD me user create karna

🔹 Certification:-
👉 Access review / approval process
Example: Manager approve kare user ka access

🔹 Report:-
👉 Basic report generate karna
Example: users list report

🔹 LiveReport:-
👉 Real-time report (UI se run hone wala)
Example: on-demand report

🔹 Workflow:-
👉 Workflow run karna
Example: joiner workflow trigger

🔹 Rule:-
👉 Custom rule execute karna
Example: custom validation logic

🔹 Maintenance:-
👉 System cleanup / maintenance
Example: old logs delete karna

🔹 SystemMaintenance:-
👉 System level maintenance
Example: DB cleanup, cache clear

🔹 TaskExecution:-
👉 Ek task ke through dusra task run karna
Example: master task → multiple tasks run

🔹 DataExport:-
👉 Data bahar export karna
Example: CSV me users export

🔹 DataImport:-
👉 Data system me import karna
Example: CSV se users load
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🚀 Version kya hota hai?
👉 Version = task definition ka version number (configuration change tracking).

👉 Jab tu task me change karega:-
arguments change

schedule change
→ version update ho sakta hai

🔹 Example:-
System.out.println(td.getVersion());
Output:-
1.0

🔹 Set Version:-
td.setVersion("2.0");
System.out.println(td.getVersion());

Output:-
2.0
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🚀 Owner kya hota hai? (IMPORTANT):-
✅ Sahi samajh:-
👉 Owner = jo user/admin task ka responsible hai
👉 Matlab:-
kisne task banaya
kaun manage karega
kaun run karega (UI se)

💡 Example:-
System.out.println(td.getOwner().getName());

Output:-
admin

🔥 Clear Difference:-
Concept	        Meaning
Owner------Task ka responsible user
Target-----Task kispe perform ho raha hai

🎯 Example samajh:-
👉 Identity Aggregation task:-
Field	   Value
Owner------admin
Target-----Active Directory
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
()Template = Ready-made blueprint / predefined configuration.
Matlab:-
Ek aisa task jo already set hota hai (config ke saath), jise baar-baar reuse kar sakte ho.

💡 Template ka matlab:-
👉 Template = reusable task design
Example:-
Ek base aggregation config → multiple tasks me reuse.

🧩 1️⃣ Template kya hota hai?
👉 Template = reusable design (ready-made config)
👉 Ek baar bana, baar-baar use karo
💡 Example:-
Template Task:
Aggregation Template
   ↓
Use karke banao:
Aggregation for AD
Aggregation for SAP
Aggregation for DB
👉 Har baar naya task likhne ki zarurat nahi.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🌳 2️⃣ Parent kya hota hai?
👉 Parent = main/master task

👉 Ye decide karta hai:-
kaunse child tasks chalenge
kis order me chalenge

💡 Example:-
Parent Task: Daily Job
👉 Iske andar multiple tasks honge

🌿 3️⃣ Child kya hota hai?
👉 Child = sub-task (parent ka part)
👉 Parent ke andar run hota hai.

💡 Example:-
Parent: Daily Job
   ↓
   ├── Child 1: Aggregation
   ├── Child 2: Identity Refresh
   ├── Child 3: Provisioning
-------------------------------------
🔥 Real Flow:-
Parent Task start
   ↓
Child Task 1 run
   ↓
Child Task 2 run
   ↓
Child Task 3 run
   ↓
Parent complete
--------------------------
💻 Code Example:-
TaskDefinition parent = new TaskDefinition();
parent.setName("Main Task");

TaskDefinition child = new TaskDefinition();
child.setName("Sub Task");

parent.addChild(child);

System.out.println(parent.getChildren());

Output:-
[Sub Task]
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🏷️ 1️⃣ Tags kya hote hain?
👉 Tags = labels / keywords jo task ko identify aur filter karne me help karte hain

💡 Example:-
Tags:-
aggregation
daily
critical

👉 UI me tu filter kar sakta hai:-
sirf “aggregation” wale tasks
sirf “critical” tasks

💻 Code:-
td.addTag("aggregation");
td.addTag("daily");
System.out.println(td.getTags());
Output:-
[aggregation, daily]

🎨 2️⃣ Icon kya hota hai?
👉 Icon = UI me task ka chhota image/symbol
💡 Example:-
Aggregation Task → 🔄 icon
Provisioning Task → ⚙️ icon
Report Task → 📊 icon
👉 Sirf UI me dikhane ke liye hota hai

💻 Code:-
td.setIcon("aggregation-icon");
System.out.println(td.getIcon());
Output:-
aggregation-icon

❓ 3️⃣ HelpKey kya hota hai?
👉 HelpKey = help/documentation ka reference key
👉 Jab user UI me help click karega → system iss key se help text dikhata hai
💡 Example:-
HelpKey: aggregation.help
👉 Ye kisi help file ya message se linked hota hai

💻 Code:-
td.setHelpKey("aggregation.help");
System.out.println(td.getHelpKey());
Output:-
aggregation.help
