-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🚀 Handler ka concept — SailPoint me:-
Handler = wo class ya code jo task ka real kaam perform karta hai.
TaskDefinition me sirf task ka blueprint/configuration hota hai (name, category, schedule, etc.)
Handler me logic hota hai ki task actually kya karega

💡 Important Points:-
Handler class hoti hai (Java class)
Ye implement karti hai SailPoint ka TaskHandler interface
Execution time pe executor handler ko call karta hai
Multiple tasks ek hi handler use kar sakte hain
Custom logic likhna ho → custom handler bana sakte ho

🏗 Handler ka kaam — Step by Step:-
Step	Kaam
1	Task start hota hai
2	Executor task ko pick karta hai
3	Executor handler class ka execute() method call karta hai
4	Handler logic perform karta hai (Aggregation, Provisioning, Certification etc.)
5	Handler result return karta hai
6	Task status update hota hai (Completed, Failed etc.)
