()validate:-
🚀 1️⃣ Purpose of validate():-
Object me koi mandatory field missing hai ya nahi
Object ke values valid hai ya nahi
Object ke internal consistency / logical rules follow ho rahe hain ya nahi
Relationship / references sahi hai ya nahi
Basically ye method task ya workflow ko run karne se pehle error-free banata hai.

🛠 2️⃣ TaskDefinition / Task / ApprovalSet / Workflow me validate() kya check karta hai
Object	                                                    Kya check karta hai
TaskDefinition:----Name, Type, Handler, Executor, Schedule, Version, Tags present hai ya nahi; Attributes valid hai ya nahi;
Child tasks / Parent relationship correct hai
Task:---------Arguments valid hai ya nahi; Executor/Handler set hai ya nahi; Timeout, Enabled, Visible values correct hai ya nahi
ApprovalSet:--Approvers set hai ya nahi; Duplicate approvers nahi; Consistency check – koi mixed approvals nahi; Approval statuses valid hai ya nahi
Workflow:--Steps defined hai ya nahi; Transitions correct hai; Actions assigned hai; End step present hai; Messages/Events valid hai
TaskResult:---Status aur CompletionStatus valid hai; Progress/PercentComplete 0-100 me hai; Messages, Warnings, Errors valid hai.

⚡ 3️⃣ Validation ke common checks:-
Mandatory Fields:-
Name, Type, Handler, Executor, Schedule, Category, etc.

Data Type / Value Check:-
Timeout ≥ 0
PercentComplete 0–100
Status enum me hona chahiye

Relationships:-
Parent/Child TaskDefinition consistency
Workflow Step transitions valid

Consistency:-
ApprovalSet → sab approved ya pending/consistent
No invalid combination

Duplicates:-
Tags unique
Approvers unique
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
✅ TaskDefinition – Real Project Code Example
import sailpoint.api.SailPointContext;
import sailpoint.object.TaskDefinition;

import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;

public class TaskDefinitionExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        SailPointContext context = null;

        try {
            // 🔹 Get SailPoint Context
            context = SailPointFactory.createContext();

            // 🔹 Load TaskDefinition by name or ID
            String taskDefName = "Certification Task Definition";
            TaskDefinition taskDef = context.getObject(TaskDefinition.class, taskDefName);

            if (taskDef == null) {
                System.out.println("TaskDefinition not found: " + taskDefName);
                return;
            }

            // ============================================
            // 1️⃣ Icon & Help Key
            // ============================================
            System.out.println("Icon: " + taskDef.getIcon());
            taskDef.setIcon("icon-certification.png");
            System.out.println("Updated Icon: " + taskDef.getIcon());

            System.out.println("Help Key: " + taskDef.getHelpKey());
            taskDef.setHelpKey("TASK_CERT_HELP");
            System.out.println("Updated Help Key: " + taskDef.getHelpKey());

            // ============================================
            // 2️⃣ Template
            // ============================================
            System.out.println("Is Template? " + taskDef.isTemplate());
            taskDef.setTemplate(true);
            System.out.println("Updated Template Flag: " + taskDef.isTemplate());

            // ============================================
            // 3️⃣ Parent & Children
            // ============================================
            TaskDefinition parentDef = taskDef.getParent();
            System.out.println("Parent TaskDefinition: " + (parentDef != null ? parentDef.getName() : "None"));

            // Set parent
            TaskDefinition newParent = context.getObject(TaskDefinition.class, "Parent TaskDef");
            taskDef.setParent(newParent);

            // Children
            List<TaskDefinition> children = taskDef.getChildren();
            System.out.println("Children count: " + (children != null ? children.size() : 0));

            // Add child
            TaskDefinition childDef = context.getObject(TaskDefinition.class, "Child TaskDef");
            taskDef.addChild(childDef);

            // Remove child
            taskDef.removeChild(childDef);

            // ============================================
            // 4️⃣ Category & SubType
            // ============================================
            System.out.println("Category: " + taskDef.getCategory());
            taskDef.setCategory("Certification");
            System.out.println("Updated Category: " + taskDef.getCategory());

            System.out.println("SubType: " + taskDef.getSubType());
            taskDef.setSubType("Quarterly");
            System.out.println("Updated SubType: " + taskDef.getSubType());

            // ============================================
            // 5️⃣ Executor & Handler
            // ============================================
            System.out.println("Executor: " + taskDef.getExecutor());
            taskDef.setExecutor("sailpoint.api.TaskExecutor");
            System.out.println("Updated Executor: " + taskDef.getExecutor());

            System.out.println("Handler: " + taskDef.getHandler());
            taskDef.setHandler("sailpoint.task.certification.Handler");
            System.out.println("Updated Handler: " + taskDef.getHandler());

            context.commitTransaction();

        } catch (Exception e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        } finally {
            if (context != null) {
                context.decache(true);
                context.close();
            }
        }
    }
}
🔥 Sample Output (Example)
Icon: default-icon.png
Updated Icon: icon-certification.png
Help Key: TASK_HELP_DEFAULT
Updated Help Key: TASK_CERT_HELP
Is Template? false
Updated Template Flag: true
Parent TaskDefinition: None
Children count: 2
Category: General
Updated Category: Certification
SubType: Standard
Updated SubType: Quarterly
Executor: sailpoint.api.DefaultExecutor
Updated Executor: sailpoint.api.TaskExecutor
Handler: sailpoint.task.DefaultHandler
Updated Handler: sailpoint.task.certification.Handler

1️⃣ taskDef.isTemplate():-
Ye boolean field hota hai jo batata hai ki ye TaskDefinition template hai ya normal task.
Template ka matlab: Ye ek reusable blueprint hota hai, jisse nayi Tasks create ki ja sakti hain.
Output Example:-
Is Template? true
Agar ye true → Task create karte waqt developer is template ko choose karke nayi task bana sakta hai.
Agar false → Ye sirf ek normal TaskDefinition hai, jo directly schedule/run hota hai.

2️⃣ taskDef.getChildren():-
Ye list of TaskDefinition objects return karta hai.
Child TaskDefinitions ka matlab: Ye parent task ke under run hone wale sub-tasks hain.
Output Example:-
Children count: 2
Child Task 1: Certification Subtask 1
Child Task 2: Certification Subtask 2
addChild() / removeChild() → developer ya SailPoint admin manage karta hai task hierarchy me.

3️⃣ taskDef.getParent():-
Ye TaskDefinition return karta hai jo current task ka parent hai.
Output Example:-
Parent TaskDefinition: Quarterly Certification Parent Task
Agar parent null → task standalone hai.

